sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: vioC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Encodes violacein synthase, part of the vioABCDE biosynthetic operon which produces violacein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.ns1:designNotes: Does not contain a stop codon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: IldR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inhibits lactate promoter in absence of lactate

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: vioE
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Encodes vioE, part of the vioABCDE biosynthetic operon which produces violacein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.ns1:designNotes: Does not contain a stop codon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7 RNAP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Transcribes genes under control of the T7 promoter, orthogonal from E.coli native transcription machinery

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: vioA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Encodes flavin-dependent L-tryptophan oxidase, part of the vioABCDE biosynthetic operon which produces violacein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.ns1:designNotes: Does not contain a stop codon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong RBS, source organism could not be identified so "synthetic" was chosen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: vioD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Encodes protodeoxyviolaceinate monooxygenase, part of the vioABCDE biosynthetic operon which produces violacein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.ns1:designNotes: Does not contain a stop codon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7 consensus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong orthogal promoter. Promotes transcription by T7 RNAP

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Lactate promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter region for IldPRD operon of E.coli, inhibited by IldR in absence of L-lactate

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: vioB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Encodes 2-imino-3-(indol-3-yl)propanoate dimerase, part of the vioABCDE biosynthetic operon which produces violacein

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PET RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Derived from pET vector, presumed to be T7-based
